videos.headline: Oklahoma State picks off Kelly's deep shot
videos.description: With Ole Miss marching on the opening drive, Chad Kelly takes a shot down field only to be picked off by Oklahoma State's Ashton Lampkin.

videos.headline: Kelly finds wide-open Core for Sugar Bowl's 1st TD
videos.description: With all day to throw, Ole Miss' Chad Kelly finds Cody Core with no one around him to walk into the end zone for the 31-yard passing touchdown and a 10-3 lead over Oklahoma State.

videos.headline: Kelly to Treadwell works for 34-yard TD
videos.description: Chad Kelly throws his second touchdown of the game, this one to Laquon Treadwell from 34 yards out, putting the Rebels up 17-3 in the Allstate Sugar Bowl.

videos.headline: Treadwell can catch, and he can throw too
videos.description: Ole Miss goes into the bag of tricks with the backwards pass to Laquon Treadwell who throws it deep to Jordan Wilkins for the huge gain to the 10 yard line.

videos.headline: Kelly to Treadwell keeps resulting in TDs
videos.description: For the second time in the game, Ole Miss' Chad Kelly finds Laquon Treadwell for a touchdown increasing the Rebels' lead to 24-3 in the Allstate Sugar Bowl.

videos.headline: Lineman shows off the hands for big-man TD
videos.description: With five seconds left in the half and at the two-yard line, Ole Miss runs another trick play throwing the backwards pass to offensive lineman Laremy Tunsil who shows off the soft hands and waltzes into the end zone.

videos.headline: Jordan Wilkins joins the Ole Miss TD party
videos.description: On the second play after recovering an Oklahoma State muffed punt, Ole Miss' Jordan Wilkins breaks free and goes 36 yards to the end zone, making it 41-6 Rebels.

videos.headline: J.W. Walsh gets 1st TD for Oklahoma State
videos.description: J.W. Walsh scrambles into the end zone from 2 yards out to get Oklahoma State its first touchdown of the Allstate Sugar Bowl.

videos.headline: Treadwell can't stop scoring TDs
videos.description: Laquon Treadwell makes it a hat trick of touchdowns, picking up this third score on a 14-yard pass from Chad Kelly to make it 48-13 Ole Miss.
